(26160, 24781, 2627, 2, 'Storyteller', '很久很久以前，在很遠很遠的沙漠，一個黑色的身影前進著，拖著沉重的鎖鏈，引著一本巨大的黑色書本，他用誘人的聲音說: "你要聽我的故事嗎?"', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 9, '[Narrator]\nA long long time ago\nIn a desert far far away\nWalked a figure dragging a thick book\nentwined by heavy chains\nHe spoke in a tempting tune:\n\n[Storyteller]\nWould you hear my story?\nA thousand souls to fill the pages\nWould you hear my story?\nNo fictional roles, no divinable stages\nWould you hear my story?\nA million years I walk through the ages\nWould you hear my story?\nA begging voice soothed their rages\nThe stories were told\nMysteries unfold\n\n[Narrator]\nRan across two the battling kingdoms\nBlood shed on the soldiers'' armors\nHow brave they fought\nHow bright they burnt\nIn his eyes a spotless paper\nIn his mouth the words rumbled\nThe ground divided, the vision spun\nTurned to light, and colored the blank page\n\n[Storyteller]\nWould you hear my story?\nA thousand souls to fill the pages\nWould you hear my story?\nA million years I walk through the ages\nWould you hear my story?\nA priceless one without any charges\nWould you be my story?\nThe tricky voice led them to the edges\nThe stories were told\nNo one dared to hear\n\nSolo\n\n[Storyteller]\nWould you be my story?\nThe one of a thousand, a precious page\nWould you be my story?\nThe stop of time line at your golden age\nWould you be my story?\nA colorful one that never decayed\nWould you be my story?\nThe favorite one hid in my cage\nThe stories were wrote\nForever be told', '', 424, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:20:53', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26161, 39906, 0, 1, '頹廢', '', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 0, 1, 7, '玩音樂的人肚子好餓  只好走到樓頂抽一根菸\r\n努力的創作沒人理你  只能無奈的喝一杯酒 \r\n我還在害怕怕我太強  沒有人知道 \r\n難道你也是和我一樣  真的那麼巧              \r\n玩樂團我們都很狼狽  有時候好象不同一隊\r\n努力的表演如癡如醉  其實無奈的接收虛偽   \r\n為什麼音樂對我來說  如此的頹廢\r\n難道你也是和我一樣  真的那麼巧 ', '', 186, '', '尤希尤', '尤希尤', '尤希尤', '', '', 0, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:24:18', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26162, 24781, 2627, 3, 'Those Left', 'Storyteller走過之處，帶走了許多，也留下了一些，但是那些留下的，卻永遠不知道發生了什麼事情? 雨天陰鬱的情境，戲劇般的轉折，給你最心碎卻又莫名的悲痛。\n', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 16, '[Diary of a young boy]\n"It is a rainy Saturday\nTom took away my favorite toy \nI punched him in his face\nBlood poured out of his noose\nMon and dad punished me and locked me in my room\nI wonder if they are my true parents”\n\n[Storyteller]\nWell I dropped by a little town\nThank you for your kind hospitality\nI told several stories to entertain the crowd\nAnd asked the same question\n"would you be my story?"\nMost of them nodded\nA few rejected\nA young ordinary boy sneaked outside in the alley\nHe said "no"\nAnd so be it\n\nChorus: [Storyteller]\nIt''s alright, I take what I need\nAs for those left, you won''t even remember me\nChorus: [Young boy]\nAn empty diary?\nIt''s so weird\nWhy am I living in this house alone?\nI am so cold\n\n[Grown-up man]\nI had a wife and two little kids\nA simple life but I''m satisfied\nIt''s a rainy day\nA Saturday for my family\nI glanced at a black-robed man dragging\na heavy chained black book outside\nI thought this man was kind of funny~~\n\n[Storyteller again]\nWell I''ve been in this town before\nWell I met you long ago\nI''d love you to be my story\nBut I must respect your will\nThis time how about a pleading yes \nOr there won''t be a second chance\nIt''s the same question: \nWould you be my story?\nYour wife said yes\nyour sons said yes\nWhat''s your decision? My dear friend\nSo it''s still a no\nThen so be it\n\nChorus: [Storyteller]\nIt''s alright, I take what need\nAs for those left, you won''t even remember me\nChorus: [Grown-up man]\nAn empty diary?\nSuspected blank page\nTry hard to recall\nAll is a blurry anarchy\n\n[Storyteller] Why bother waste your time searching?\n[Grown-up man] I know the clues must be somewhere\n[Storyteller] Why bother follow my footsteps?\n[Grown-up man] I know you are intriguing something on the road\n[Storyteller] I''m just a humble/harmless storyteller\n[Grown-up man] Save your lies I will uncover your mask\n[Storyteller] Well would you like some pleasant stories?\n[Grown-up man] I''ll close my ears and reject all your words\n\n\nChorus: [Storyteller]\nIt''s alright\nI won''t hurt you\nSleep and forget\nNever will you know me\nChorus: [Grown-up man]\nWhere am I?\nWhat is this place?\nWhy does the figure in the far horizon look so acquainted to me', '', 427, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:26:40', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26163, 24781, 2627, 4, 'Ride The Wind', '乘著風，手持閃電，進入一個全新的世界!!\r\n\r\n"無聊的日子，無意義的爭執，我知道有更好的世界存在，只要我相信。\r\n飛在天空中，我曾夢見這一幕，奇異的光芒不知從何方射出，漩渦構成了\r\n一道水晶門，乘著風，持著閃電，進入一個全新、未知的世界"', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 1, 'Just another lonely day\r\nJust another boring day\r\nI wonder why the world keeps turning\r\nJust another nameless street\r\nJust another meaningless strife\r\nCan''t forget your words about the new world\r\n\r\nOne must believe to see it\r\nOne must be strong to face it\r\nIt sounds like me oh it''s so perfect\r\nOne must be so determined\r\nOne must be free of his mind\r\nLeave nothing behind\r\nHis new life\r\n\r\nChorus1:\r\nFlying high in the sky\r\nI''ve dreamed of this long before\r\nascension of a man\r\nSpread the clouds\r\nNow gaze into the stars\r\nIt''s coming now\r\nIt''s coming over (closer)\r\nRight! Amazing lights shoot from nowhere\r\nThe vortex constructs a crystal gate\r\nRide the wind and seize the lightning blades\r\nInto the new world a different path\r\n\r\nNot another lonely day\r\nNot another boring day\r\nI am looking forward what the new world will bring me\r\nNot another senseless pain\r\nNot another soulless plan\r\nI keep on fighting to test my own faith\r\n\r\nI believe it so I can see it\r\nI''m strong so I can face it\r\nin the world full of surprise and danger\r\nUndoubtedly so determined\r\nUnlimited imagination\r\nFinally I find my own place\r\nChorus2:\r\nInto the new world a better place\r\n\r\nSolo\r\n\r\nChorus3:\r\nInto the new world a better place', '', 333, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:29:57', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26164, 24781, 2627, 5, 'The Hunters', '"陰鬱的森林內，獵人們追逐著受傷的鹿，徬徨無措的獵物逃竄到了已荒廢的眾神殿，忠心的沉默守衛者秒殺了獵人們，毫無戲份的主角獵人們的故事到此結束...."\r\n', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 9, '[Wounded Deer]\r\nEyes surrounding me\r\nBlades are all around\r\nTraps are set to inveigle me\r\nWell I''d better believe\r\nThere''s no way out\r\nDangers lurk within\r\nWhere once were safe are \r\nnow full of risk\r\n\r\nWhere sunlight''s burning\r\nSlow creak''s boiling\r\nPebbles are stabbing\r\nFrantically staggering\r\nStone wall''s rising\r\nStatues are moving\r\nNowhere to run nowhere to hide\r\n\r\nBridge:\r\nDark clouds shroud without a sign\r\nThe sigil of death are marked on the hunters brows\r\nBlue beams emitted from the statue''s eyes\r\nSwift execution without a fight\r\nThe hunters lie in their own cold blood\r\n\r\n[Protector of the forest]\r\nWe were the chosen ones\r\nChampions from different time\r\nDelegated to guard the temple of gods\r\nHope you comprehend\r\nAges passed by\r\nSeeds had grow into trees\r\nGarden had turned into a forest\r\n\r\nCovered by dust\r\nBuried in sand\r\nWe are you guardians in silence \r\nFoolish hunters\r\nDared to trespass\r\nDeath is the redemption of your blasphemy\r\n\r\nChorus1:\r\nThe hunters, dead hunters\r\nIn the veil of mist\r\nUnder perverted sky\r\nThe hunters, dead hunters\r\nIn the status of peace\r\nUnder saturnine trees\r\n\r\nSolo\r\nRitual in the forest\r\n\r\nChorus2', '', 378, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:36:02', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
