(26166, 24781, 2627, 7, 'Forsaken Knights', '在Besieged發生前的12小時，忠心耿耿的流浪騎士們快馬加鞭，來得急到達即將淪陷的家園嗎?', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 9, 'In the darkest corner\nFar beyond our homeland\nSentenced and banished for a lifetime\nTo this barren boarder\nConvicted of a trumped-up charge\nToo much justice for a corrupted court\nLost the power\nLost the favour \nWe were driven away in the name of betrayal\n\nChorus1:\nWhy are we here?\nStarving and thirsty\nOnce the noble knights\nNow the walking dead\nGoddess of Righteousness\nSave us from the depths of hell\nGive us a chance to \nWash our name clean\n\nIn the morning sun\nTraining to keep our strength \nThe arms of steel the hearts of gold\nConcentrating on the skills\nRelives us from our shame\nWe are watching\nAnd always be prepared\n\nBridge:\n[Raiders]\nThe gate is wide-open \nThose horse riders are gone\nNow it''s time to swallow this fat goat\nRide on to our victory \n\n[Kings speech]\nWelcome! Today we are here to celebrate the harvest\nThanks to me, your wise king\nLong live the king (Long live!!)\n\nChorus2:\nOur land is in great peril\nRestlessly we spur forward\nSave our kingdom\nSave the king\nThrough the mountains\nCross the rivers\nWon''t recant our creed\nMy beloved nation\nThou shall not fall\n\nSolo\n\nChorus3\n', '', 409, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:38:58', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26167, 24781, 2627, 8, 'Serene Sky', '毀滅的世界，最後一位旅客，究竟這是一個全新的開始，或是這是一個全然的黑暗呢?他找尋著熟悉的星光，滿懷著希望往下一個方向前去....', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 3, 'Day:\r\nWater splashes on my feet\r\nSo warm like it has been heated\r\nNo winds no breeze\r\nAs if the air has halted flowing (blowing)\r\n\r\nSweat falls from my arms\r\nAs the sun scorches the skins\r\nTry to bear this sultriness\r\nAnd fight the faintness \r\n\r\nChorus1: \r\nIs anybody here?\r\nI cry loud to be heard\r\nIn this debris, wasteland\r\nLifeless planet earth\r\nStruggle to step \r\nForward to somewhere\r\nMaybe there''s still hope in my mind\r\n\r\nNight:\r\nStrange stars in the serene sky\r\nTwo half moons light the darkness\r\nCold as the frigid winter\r\nTry to find a cave to fit in \r\nWill someone find me\r\nI think I hear something there\r\nOutside a field of death\r\nStorm clouds are now approaching\r\n\r\nChorus2:\r\nIs anybody here?\r\nI cry loud to be heard\r\nIn this debris, wasteland\r\nLifeless planet earth\r\nEach step takes enormous pain\r\nForward to somewhere else\r\nCould it be the last hope hid in my fragile mind?\r\n\r\nChorus3:\r\nCould it be a new start\r\nOr it just a new dark\r\nLooking for a known star\r\nHopefully I depart', '', 386, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:41:08', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26168, 24781, 2627, 9, 'Hero''s Day Off', '英雄休假日，每週這短短的一天相信不會有什麼大事件發生才是。', '2010-06-30 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 1, '[Theme of the hero]\r\n“He fights crimes\r\n  And saves our lives\r\n  The symbol of courage\r\n  A true savior\r\n  Our hero\r\n  Look after us\r\n  Go get them tiger\r\n  May justice prevail”\r\n\r\nAfter 5 days 23 hours of hard work\r\nthis morning I slept in bed\r\nNo disturbance no alarm\r\nI wake up at the noon\r\n\r\nChorus1:\r\nIt''s a hero''s day off\r\nJustice could wait a day\r\nI wear no suit and leave the mask at home\r\nNo job today\r\nThe villain won''t do much damage\r\n''cause nothing I can''t mend\r\nEnjoy the carefree moment\r\nCelebrate my deeds these days\r\n\r\nOff duty \r\n\r\nI walk out for some fresh air\r\nand have a perfect launch\r\nwalk into a supermarket to buy some groceries (eh~~~)\r\n\r\n[Robber]\r\n“Freeze, it''s a robbery\r\n  Everybody get down on the floor\r\n  Everybody be cool\r\n  You! Cashiers, put the money in the bags\r\n  Do exactly what I say and nobody gets hurt”\r\n\r\n[Hero]\r\nWhat a joke?\r\nRob in front of me\r\nWhat a junk?\r\nOops~ but not today \r\n\r\nChorus2:\r\nIt''s a hero''s day off \r\nSorry I can''t help today\r\nStick to the rules\r\nI just can''t do anything\r\nHold on tight\r\nand wait for a few more hours\r\nBut rest assured\r\nTomorrow justice will prevail\r\nJustice will prevail\r\n\r\nSolo\r\n\r\nChorus3', '', 278, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'Vicnest Music Studio', '', 1, 1, 0, '2010-06-30 13:42:31', '2015-03-12 13:42:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
